{
  "question_id": "b072b37f-24ff-4b18-b2a2-0e9dbcb9aba6",
  "short_text": "M pattern with * - 2",
  "content": "Given a number `N`, write a program to print the letter **M** of `N` rows with two **Solid Pyramids** using stars (`*`).\r\n\r\n````\r\n   *       * \r\n  * *     * * \r\n * * *   * * * \r\n* * * * * * * *\r\n````\r\n\r\n<MultiLineNote>\r\nThere is a space after every star (`*`).\r\n</MultiLineNote>\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n#### Input\r\n\r\nThe input will be a single line containing an integer representing `N`.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n#### Output\r\n\r\nThe output should be `N` rows containing stars (`*`) as the letter **M** shown in the sample output.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n#### Explanation\r\n\r\nFor example, if the given number is `N = 4`, \r\n\r\n- Print the stars (`*`) on **4** rows as shown in the given image.\r\n\r\n<Img imageSrc='https://assets.ccbp.in/frontend/content/programming-foundations/cx-mpattern-with-stars-2.png' widthPercent='100'/>\r\n\r\n\r\n<MultiLineNote>\r\nIn the given image,\r\n\r\n- The Empty box indicates a space (\" \").\r\n- The Star in the box indicates a star (\"*\").\r\n</MultiLineNote>\r\n\r\n\r\nThe output should be,\r\n\r\n````\r\n   *       * \r\n  * *     * * \r\n * * *   * * * \r\n* * * * * * * *\r\n````",
  "question_type": "CODING",
  "content_type": "MARKDOWN",
  "codes": [
    {
      "code_id": "e3e757fd-ea02-4b48-b625-d1c4fb77c618",
      "code_content": "rows = int(input())\n\nfor each_row in range(1, rows + 1):\n    first_pyramid_spaces = \" \" * (rows - each_row)\n    first_pyramid_stars = \"* \" * each_row\n    first_pyramid = first_pyramid_spaces + first_pyramid_stars\n    \n    space_between_pyramids = \" \" * (rows - each_row)\n    \n    second_pyramid_spaces = \" \" * (rows - each_row)\n    second_pyramid_stars = \"* \" * each_row\n    second_pyramid = second_pyramid_spaces + second_pyramid_stars\n    \n    print(first_pyramid + space_between_pyramids + second_pyramid)",
      "language": "PYTHON",
      "default_code": true
    }
  ],
